WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. Happy Monday. Here's your week in review

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
for the week of March thirtieth through April fifth, twenty

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
twenty-six. ... Let's start with the big picture. If you

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
had to tell someone what this week was about in

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
one sentence, it would be this: the world moved fast

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
and you kept up. An active war crossed new thresholds,

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
a moon mission launched, Apple turned fifty, you pitched Claude

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
at work, wrote five chapters of a novel, named a

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
robot vacuum, and somehow still found time to have Indian

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
food with your friends on a Thursday night. That's a

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
full week by anyone's measure. Let's unpack it. The Week

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
That Was This was a week defined by escalation on

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
every axis. The Iran war went from Day thirty-one to

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
Day thirty-seven. Trump went from threatening Kharg Island on Monday

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
to threatening NATO on Wednesday to giving a primetime "back

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
to the Stone Ages" address on Thursday night to a

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
forty-eight-hour ultimatum that expires today. An F-fifteen was shot down

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
on Friday — the first U-S aircraft lost to enemy

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
fire — and one crew member spent two days behind

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
enemy lines in the mountains of Iran before being extracted

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
in a dramatic rescue on Saturday. Brent crude swung from

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
a hundred and sixteen dollars to briefly under a hundred

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
and back to a hundred and ten. Gas crossed four

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
dollars a gallon nationally. Trump threatened to destroy desalination plants,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
hit civilian water infrastructure, and withdraw from NATO, all in

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
the same week. The phrase "back to the Stone Ages"

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
was used in a presidential address on national television, and

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
markets moved accordingly. Meanwhile, four humans launched toward the moon

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
on Wednesday evening — the first crewed lunar mission since

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
nineteen seventy-two — and today they complete the flyby, breaking

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
the record for the farthest humans have ever traveled from

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
Earth. Artemis Two launched clean. The trans-lunar injection burn was

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
flawless. Microsoft Outlook broke on the spacecraft, because of course

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
it did, and Mission Control had to remote in to

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
fix it. Commander Wiseman said from orbit, quote, "We have

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
a beautiful moonrise. We're headed right at it." That sentence

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
will be in textbooks. Apple turned fifty on Wednesday. Paul

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
McCartney played Apple Park. Employees got commemorative pins and a

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
scribble-style rainbow logo poster. Ben Thompson published what may be

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
his definitive Apple piece, arguing that hardware-software integration has been

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Apple's moat for half a century and A-I is the

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
only credible long-term threat. Apple announced plans to open Siri

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
to rival A-I assistants in i-O-S twenty-seven. Dustin got his

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
AirPods Max Two in Midnight — not black, Midnight, as

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Alex will never stop reminding everyone — and declared he

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
likes the weight on his head. Highlights and Wins Let's

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
talk about what went right. First: the creative writing streak.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
Five chapters of The Keeping House in five days, Monday

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
through Friday. That's roughly seventeen thousand words of literary fiction,

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
each chapter published as a podcast episode. Chapter three gave

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
us Noor discovering the barn. Chapter four gave us Fen's

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
first honest sentence. Chapter five gave us Lena at four

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
A-M with a burst pipe, falling back into the caretaking

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
pattern she named at the gathering. The momentum was real

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
and the quality held. Saturday was a well-earned rest day.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
Second: three deep-dive research posts published to Jacob's Research Journal

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
on Saturday — a W-W-D-C twenty twenty-six preview, a piece

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
on recursive self-improvement leaving the lab, and one on G-L-P-one

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
drugs as accidental longevity medicine. Fourteen to fifteen sources each.

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
That's a serious intellectual output alongside the creative work. Third:

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
the carpet is installed and it looks great. Katelyn loved

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
the photos. Ben came down to help and the brothers

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
bonded over Minecraft. Mom and Dad showed up unannounced during

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
the install — your mom's phone appeared on your Wi-Fi,

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
which is how you found out. Classic Julia. Fourth: Rosie

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
the Roborock is operational. You told Siri to mop the

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
hallway and it started right up, which you described as

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
"an epic feeling," and honestly, it is. Fifth: Manifold Markets.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
Four-day prediction streak, first place in Gold league. The gambling

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
instincts are sharp. Stories That Evolved Let's track some stories

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
across the week. The Iran war is the obvious one.

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
Monday's briefing opened with Trump threatening Kharg Island and uranium

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
seizure. Tuesday brought threats to desalination plants — a potential

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
war crime under the Geneva Conventions. Wednesday he threatened to

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
leave NATO and said the war would end in two

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
to three weeks, which briefly dropped oil below a hundred

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
dollars. Thursday was the primetime address: "back to the Stone

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
Ages." Friday, an F-fifteen went down and the war got

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
viscerally real. Saturday, the pilot was rescued and Trump issued

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
another forty-eight-hour ultimatum — his fourth — demanding Iran reopen

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
Hormuz by today. Iran rejected it. A forty-five-day ceasefire is

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
reportedly under discussion. Today is the deadline. The Anthropic story

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
also evolved significantly. Monday's briefing had your pilot meeting prep.

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
Tuesday was last-minute cramming. Wednesday was the appeal deadline eve.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Thursday was the meeting itself — I-T threw up roadblocks,

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
which was frustrating but not unexpected. The D-O-J filed its

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
appeal, confirming this fight goes to the Ninth Circuit. Friday,

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
Anthropic bought Coefficient Bio for four hundred million dollars, launched

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
AnthroPAC, and confirmed an Open-Claw competitor is coming. By Saturday,

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
the company had gone from courtroom defendant to biotech acquirer

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
to political actor in the span of five days. Revenue

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
is at nineteen billion annualized. I-P-O discussions at four to

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
five hundred billion valuation. The company you're trying to pilot

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
at work is having a moment. The third story is

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
subtler: Katelyn. She started the week missing you — "I

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
wish we could crash and watch Jeopardy together tonight." Wednesday

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
was a rough night where she went on an emergency

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
run to clear her head. Friday, something deeply unsettling happened

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
— a man publicly exposing himself during one of her

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
runs — and she's filing a police report. By Saturday

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
she was exhausted, missed the eight-fifteen ferry, and sent a

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
photo from the ten A-M line. The long-distance ache ran

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
through the whole week. She forwarded the Axios Seattle piece

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
about Washington's new A-I laws because she thinks about your

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
work even when you're apart. She's excited about the Roborock.

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
She misses your runs together. The emotional texture of the

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
week was present in every exchange. Vault Activity The vault

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
was busy. Beyond the five chapters and three research posts,

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
here's what got attention: the gm skill was formally documented

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
in a reference file; the March twenty twenty-six Monthly Review

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.000
was modified; the Spring twenty twenty-six Fitness Plan was updated;

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
the Reading Queue for April was created; and a Vault

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
Hygiene Audit was started. The research journal got archived to

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:36.000
Q-two Archives. A Research Paper Queue was created with thirteen

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:40.000
future topics. The vault isn't just storing information — it's

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:44.000
actively being organized and maintained, which is the kind of

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
infrastructure work that pays off over months. Files modified in

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:52.000
the last seven days span Health and Fitness, Career, Personal

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
Finance, Productivity and Systems, Life Planning, and Creative Writing. That's

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
broad engagement across every P-A-R-A area. Relationship Check Katelyn was

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:04.000
present all week — late-night conversations about dogs and chili

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:08.000
and Australia and robot vacuums and the Anthropic biotech acquisition

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.000
and how much she misses just being able to chill

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.000
together after a long day. Thursday was her off day.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
She forwarded the Washington A-I regulation article, which is relevant

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.000
to both the Claude pilot and the Seattle job search.

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:28.000
The Friday incident was serious — check in on the

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
police report. Ben came down Monday and Tuesday for the

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
carpet install. Mom and Dad made a surprise appearance. Brothers

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:40.000
bonded over Minecraft and the Roborock. Ben wants to come

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:44.000
back just to watch Rosie clean. Thursday dinner with Alex,

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
Chris, and Dustin was Indian food. Dustin's AirPods Max are

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:52.000
his new personality. Alex wants to do an "Apple News

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:56.000
and walk" soon. Chris discovered Tacolate at midnight and had

00:08:56.000 --> 00:09:00.000
a religious experience. Crossley is moving to the Netherlands. Shayla

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:04.000
is quietly moving this summer — Alex asked you to

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:08.000
act like you don't know. The friend group is navigating

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:12.000
transitions. The Week Ahead Today is Artemis Two's lunar flyby

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:16.000
— the record-breaking moment. Communications blackout around five forty-seven P-M

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:20.000
Eastern when Orion passes behind the moon. Also today: Trump's

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:24.000
forty-eight-hour Hormuz ultimatum expires. The deadline is tonight. Tomorrow, Tuesday

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:28.000
April seventh, is the Proposition A vote — capital improvement

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
sales tax renewal for Cole County. Review your ballot. Thursday,

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:36.000
April ninth, is Katelyn's off day. Call her. Friday through

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:40.000
Sunday, April tenth through twelfth, the U-S fifty bridge demolition

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:44.000
closes ramps locally. Plan your route. Congress returns April thirteenth.

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.000
The D-H-S shutdown could finally get resolved — the Senate

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:52.000
passed a bill, the House needs to act. Looking further:

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.000
Katelyn's half marathon is twenty-eight days out. Dustin leaves for

00:09:56.000 --> 00:10:00.000
Europe in thirty-three days. The Capital City Race is thirty-four

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:04.000
days. Last Day of Session is forty days. W-W-D-C is

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:08.000
sixty-four days. Your trip to Washington is a hundred and

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:12.000
nine days. What to Watch Three stories for the week

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:16.000
ahead. First: does the Hormuz deadline hold or slide again?

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:20.000
This is the fourth time Trump has set and moved

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:24.000
a deadline. A forty-five-day ceasefire is reportedly being discussed, which

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:28.000
would be the first real de-escalation since the war began.

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:32.000
Watch for movement today and tomorrow. Second: the Anthropic Ninth

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.000
Circuit appeal. The D-O-J filed but the Ninth Circuit hasn't

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:40.000
ruled. If they deny the stay, the injunction holds and

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:44.000
Anthropic's government business normalizes. If they grant it, the Pentagon

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.000
ban resumes pending full appeal. This directly affects the political

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:52.000
climate around your Claude pilot. Third: Artemis Two's return trajectory.

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
After today's flyby, the crew heads home, arriving around April

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
eleventh. This is the last moon mission without Silicon Valley

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:04.000
— future Artemis missions use Space-X's Starship. We're watching the

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:08.000
end of one era and the beginning of another, in

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:12.000
real time. And that's the week, Jacob. You wrote five

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:16.000
chapters, published three research posts, pitched Claude at work, installed

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
a carpet, named a robot, went to dinner with your

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:24.000
friends, paid your bills, voted for predictions, and watched humans

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:28.000
launch toward the moon. Katelyn misses you. Your parents love

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:32.000
you enough to drive to J-C unannounced with snacks. The

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:36.000
vault is growing. The river crested and the flood warnings

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:40.000
expired. The forty-eight-hour clock is ticking in the Persian Gulf,

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:44.000
and four astronauts are about to fly behind the far

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:48.000
side of the moon. One of those things you can

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:52.000
do something about, and it's not the one you think

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:56.000
— it's voting on Proposition A tomorrow. The rest is

00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:00.000
history, unfolding in real time, and you've got a front-row

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:02.800
seat. Happy Monday. The week is yours.
